    "Table 2 shows the average solve time for each problem size across 30 instances using MOSEK.",
    "(Solve times with open-source solvers such as Clarabel were a bit longer.)",
    "We can see that even very large problems can be solved with stunning speed.",
    "We solved many more problems than those shown in table 2, and used the solve times to fit a log-log model, approximating the solve time as an b k c, with parameters a, b, c. We obtained coefficients b = 0.79 and c = 1.72, consistent with the theoretical scaling of O(nk 2).",
